      "note_no": "5931",
      "note": "What was the Great Sign? Some Commentators understand by it the \"White Shining Hand\": see n. 2550 to 20:22-23. Others think it was the miracle of the rod that became a \"snake active in motion\": see 20:20, n. 2549. These were among the Greater Signs: 20:23. In 17:101 there is a reference to nine clear Signs given to Moses, and these are specified in detail in n. 1091 to 7:133. the fact is, there were many Signs given, \"openly self-explained,\" but Pharaoh and his men \"were steeped in arrogance-a people given to sin\" (7:133). the pre-eminently Great Sign was therefore the fact of Moses being sent to Pharaoh, which subsequently converted the magicians and the more learned Egyptians to the true God (20:70-73), though Pharaoh and his Chiefs resisted and suffered for their sins. (R)."
